ximately equal to the mean density obtained from the star's\neffective temperature and luminosity.\n  Despite limited frequency resolution of the MOST data, we were able to\nrecover the closely-spaced SPB frequency quadruplet discovered from the ground\nin 2002-2004. The other two SPB terms seen from the ground were also recovered.\nMoreover, our analysis of the MOST data adds 15 low-amplitude SPB terms with\nfrequencies ranging from 0.109 c/d to 2.786 c/d.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Mar 2013 12:49:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
